26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_engine_disp_dmacnv50.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:31 riastradh Exp $");

29#include "dmacnv50.h"
30#include "rootnv50.h"
31
32#include <core/client.h>
33#include <core/oproxy.h>
34#include <core/ramht.h>
35#include <subdev/fb.h>
36#include <subdev/timer.h>
37#include <engine/dma.h>
38
39struct nv50_disp_dmac_object {
40 struct nvkm_oproxy oproxy;
41 struct nv50_disp_root *root;
42 int hash;
43};
44
45static void
46nv50_disp_dmac_child_del_(struct nvkm_oproxy *base)
47{
48 struct nv50_disp_dmac_object *object =
49 container_of(base, typeof(*object), oproxy);
50 nvkm_ramht_remove(object->root->ramht, object->hash);
51}
52
53static const struct nvkm_oproxy_func
54nv50_disp_dmac_child_func_ = {
55 .dtor[0] = nv50_disp_dmac_child_del_,
56};
57
58static int
59nv50_disp_dmac_child_new_(struct nv50_disp_chan *base,
60 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
61 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
62{
63 struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan = nv50_disp_dmac(base);
64 struct nv50_disp_root *root = chan->base.root;
65 struct nvkm_device *device = root->disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
66 const struct nvkm_device_oclass *sclass = oclass->priv;
67 struct nv50_disp_dmac_object *object;
68 int ret;
69
70 if (!(object = kzalloc(sizeof(*object), GFP_KERNEL)))
71 return -ENOMEM;
72 nvkm_oproxy_ctor(&nv50_disp_dmac_child_func_, oclass, &object->oproxy);
73 object->root = root;
74 *pobject = &object->oproxy.base;
75
76 ret = sclass->ctor(device, oclass, data, size, &object->oproxy.object);
77 if (ret)
78 return ret;
79
80 object->hash = chan->func->bind(chan, object->oproxy.object,
81 oclass->handle);
82 if (object->hash < 0)
83 return object->hash;
84
85 return 0;
86}
87
88static int
89nv50_disp_dmac_child_get_(struct nv50_disp_chan *base, int index,
90 struct nvkm_oclass *sclass)
91{
92 struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan = nv50_disp_dmac(base);
93 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->base.root->disp;
94 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
95 const struct nvkm_device_oclass *oclass = NULL;
96
97 sclass->engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, NVKM_ENGINE_DMAOBJ);
98 if (sclass->engine && sclass->engine->func->base.sclass) {
99 sclass->engine->func->base.sclass(sclass, index, &oclass);
100 if (oclass) {
101 sclass->priv = oclass;
102 return 0;
103 }
104 }
105
106 return -EINVAL;
107}
108
109static void
110nv50_disp_dmac_fini_(struct nv50_disp_chan *base)
111{
112 struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan = nv50_disp_dmac(base);
113 chan->func->fini(chan);
114}
115
116static int
117nv50_disp_dmac_init_(struct nv50_disp_chan *base)
118{
119 struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan = nv50_disp_dmac(base);
120 return chan->func->init(chan);
121}
122
123static void *
124nv50_disp_dmac_dtor_(struct nv50_disp_chan *base)
125{
126 return nv50_disp_dmac(base);
127}
128
129static const struct nv50_disp_chan_func
130nv50_disp_dmac_func_ = {
131 .dtor = nv50_disp_dmac_dtor_,
132 .init = nv50_disp_dmac_init_,
133 .fini = nv50_disp_dmac_fini_,
134 .child_get = nv50_disp_dmac_child_get_,
135 .child_new = nv50_disp_dmac_child_new_,
136};
137
138int
139nv50_disp_dmac_new_(const struct nv50_disp_dmac_func *func,
140 const struct nv50_disp_chan_mthd *mthd,
141 struct nv50_disp_root *root, int chid, int head, u64 push,
142 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
143 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
144{
145 struct nvkm_device *device = root->disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
146 struct nvkm_client *client = oclass->client;
147 struct nvkm_dmaobj *dmaobj;
148 struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan;
149 int ret;
150
151 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
152 return -ENOMEM;
153 *pobject = &chan->base.object;
154 chan->func = func;
155
156 ret = nv50_disp_chan_ctor(&nv50_disp_dmac_func_, mthd, root,
157 chid, head, oclass, &chan->base);
158 if (ret)
159 return ret;
160
161 dmaobj = nvkm_dma_search(device->dma, client, push);
162 if (!dmaobj)
163 return -ENOENT;
164
165 if (dmaobj->limit - dmaobj->start != 0xfff)
166 return -EINVAL;
167
168 switch (dmaobj->target) {
169 case NV_MEM_TARGET_VRAM:
170 chan->push = 0x00000001 | dmaobj->start >> 8;
171 break;
172 case NV_MEM_TARGET_PCI_NOSNOOP:
173 chan->push = 0x00000003 | dmaobj->start >> 8;
174 break;
175 default:
176 return -EINVAL;
177 }
178
179 return 0;
180}
181
182int
183nv50_disp_dmac_bind(struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan,
184 struct nvkm_object *object, u32 handle)
185{
186 return nvkm_ramht_insert(chan->base.root->ramht, object,
187 chan->base.chid, -10, handle,
188 chan->base.chid << 28 |
189 chan->base.chid);
190}
191
192static void
193nv50_disp_dmac_fini(struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan)
194{
195 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->base.root->disp;
196 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
197 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
198 int chid = chan->base.chid;
199
200 /* deactivate channel */
201 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x0010), 0x00001010, 0x00001000);
202 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x0010), 0x00000003, 0x00000000);
203 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
204 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x10)) & 0x001e0000))
205 break;
206 ) < 0) {
207 nvkm_error(subdev, "ch %d fini timeout, %08x\n", chid,
208 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x10)));
209 }
210
211 /* disable error reporting and completion notifications */
212 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610028, 0x00010001 << chid, 0x00000000 << chid);
213}
214
215static int
216nv50_disp_dmac_init(struct nv50_disp_dmac *chan)
217{
218 struct nv50_disp *disp = chan->base.root->disp;
219 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
220 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
221 int chid = chan->base.chid;
222
223 /* enable error reporting */
224 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610028, 0x00010000 << chid, 0x00010000 << chid);
225
226 /* initialise channel for dma command submission */
227 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610204 + (chid * 0x0010), chan->push);
228 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610208 + (chid * 0x0010), 0x00010000);
229 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61020c + (chid * 0x0010), chid);
230 nvkm_mask(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x0010), 0x00000010, 0x00000010);
231 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x640000 + (chid * 0x1000), 0x00000000);
232 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x0010), 0x00000013);
233
234 /* wait for it to go inactive */
235 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
236 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x10)) & 0x80000000))
237 break;
238 ) < 0) {
239 nvkm_error(subdev, "ch %d init timeout, %08x\n", chid,
240 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610200 + (chid * 0x10)));
241 return -EBUSY;
242 }
243
244 return 0;
245}
246
247const struct nv50_disp_dmac_func
248nv50_disp_dmac_func = {
249 .init = nv50_disp_dmac_init,
250 .fini = nv50_disp_dmac_fini,
251 .bind = nv50_disp_dmac_bind,
252};
